'''佩罗桥'''（{{lang|en|Pero's Bridge}}）是英格兰[[布里斯托尔|布里斯托尔]]的一座行人[[上開橋|上開橋]]，跨布里斯托尔港的圣奥古斯丁水道（{{lang|en|St Augustine's Reach}}）。两端分别连接[[皇后广场_(布里斯托尔)|皇后广场]]和[[千禧广场_(布里斯托尔)|千禧广场]]。

这座桥得名于佩罗·琼斯（1753-1798年），1783年从[[加勒比海|加勒比海]]的[[尼维斯岛|尼维斯岛]]来到布里斯托尔，是大乔治街7号[[乔治府|乔治府]]商人约翰·平尼（1740-1818）的奴隶。<ref>{{cite web | title=Pero's Bridge | work=History Footsteps | url=http://www.englandpast.net/education/legacy2.html | accessdate=2006-08-19| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070811005124/http://www.englandpast.net/education/legacy2.html | archivedate=2007-08-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=Bristol's Georgian House Museum | work=Bristol City Council | url=http://www.bristol-city.gov.uk/ccm/content/Leisure-Culture/Museums-Galleries/georgian-house-city-museums-and-art-gallery.en | accessdate=2006-08-19|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20060813185322/http://www.bristol-city.gov.uk/ccm/content/Leisure-Culture/Museums-Galleries/georgian-house-city-museums-and-art-gallery.en|archivedate = 2006-08-13}}</ref>

== 历史 ==

这座桥由爱尔兰艺术家艾利斯·奥康奈尔与[[奧雅納|奧雅納]]公司共同设计。<ref name="#1">{{cite web|title=Eilis O Connell Biography|url=http://www.eilisoconnell.com/Pages/Biography.htm|work=Eilis O Connel sculptor|accessdate=2013-07-31|archive-date=2018-05-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180510012429/http://www.eilisoconnell.com/Pages/Biography.htm|dead-url=yes}}</ref> It was formally opened in 1999 by [[Paul_Boateng|Paul Boateng]] MP, then a [[Home_Office|Home Office]] minister.<ref name=WDP01>{{cite news|last=Nicks|first=Gary|title=Bridge to a future of racial harmony|url=http://www.lexisnexis.com/uk/nexis/results/docview/docview.do?docLinkInd=true&risb=21_T17888363495&format=GNBFI&sort=BOOLEAN&startDocNo=1&resultsUrlKey=29_T17888363490&cisb=22_T17888363497&treeMax=true&treeWidth=0&csi=166254&docNo=9|accessdate=2013-07-31|newspaper=Western Daily Press|date=1999-03-17 }}</ref><ref name="#1"/> 1999年由当时[[英國內政部|英國內政部]]大臣保罗·博阿滕议员正式揭幕开通。<ref name=WDP01 />这座桥的名称遭到了当时的[[自由民主党_(英国)|自由民主党]]议员[[史提芬·威廉斯|史提芬·威廉斯]]的攻击。他谴责这一决定是"姿态政治"，希望建立一座雕像或永久纪念碑来纪念布里斯托尔在奴隶贸易中的作用。<ref>{{cite news |last1=Booth |first1=Martin |title=THE UNTOLD HISTORY OF PERO’S BRIDGE |url=https://www.bristol247.com/news-and-features/features/untold-history-peros-bridge/ |accessdate=2020-06-15 |work=Bristol 24/7 |date=2020-06-14 |archive-date=2020-11-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101033751/https://www.bristol247.com/news-and-features/features/untold-history-peros-bridge/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=BEP01>{{cite news|last=Onions|first=Ian|title=Slave Bridge Attack; New name a snub to city benefactor|url=http://www.lexisnexis.com/uk/nexis/results/docview/docview.do?docLinkInd=true&risb=21_T17888363495&format=GNBFI&sort=BOOLEAN&startDocNo=1&resultsUrlKey=29_T17888363490&cisb=22_T17888363497&treeMax=true&treeWidth=0&csi=166254&docNo=8|accessdate=2013-07-31|newspaper=Bristol Evening Post|date=1998-11-17|format= subscription required}}</ref>
现在，成百上千的人把挂锁贴在桥上，以示对彼此的感情。

2020年6月，在[[乔治·弗洛伊德之死引发的示威活动|乔治·弗洛伊德之死引发的示威活动]]期间，布里斯托尔奴隶贩子[[爱德华·科尔斯顿|爱德华·科尔斯顿]]的青铜雕像[[乔治·弗洛伊德之死引发的拆除历史争议人物雕像浪潮|被抗议者从桥上推到河中]]，当局将其打捞上来，保存起来<ref>{{Cite news|date=2020-06-11|title=Edward Colston statue pulled out of Bristol Harbour|language=en-GB|work=BBC News|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-bristol-53004748|access-date=2020-10-01|archive-date=2020-06-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200611061748/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-bristol-53004748|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

